From Floyd Norris’s High & Low Finance:

If I ran a radio station, the bankruptcy filing by General Motors would be marked by a day of songs inspired by the company that once dominated America’s wheels-based culture.

I’d start with “409” by the Beach Boys. The 409 was the ultimate Chevy engine.

Then I’d play “G.T.O.” by Ronny and the Daytonas, about the Pontiac muscle car that kids dreamed of in my youth.

